node.text:
#ad Are your pens and markers all over the place? I know mine are! Thankfully, now I have this writing utensil organizer that I crafted using products from Michaels!

I've teamed up with @Michaelsstores and created an easy back to school project to keep you organized for the new year! I love using their Creatology products for all my crafting needs! What are some of your favorite back to school products from Michaels?! #makeitwithmichaels

node.text:
I have teamed up with some great educators for the Teach for Justice Campaign! Today I’m sharing how I conducted a library analysis for my own classroom library. I have only done this once so if you have any tips or ideas on some things to change let me know! I am learning along with you! 

If you want the resources, I compiled everything into a google sheet for you! Bit.ly/2B9ps2N 

Check out all the other amazing lessons with the hashtag #teachforjusticecampaign

#teachersofinstagram #teachersfollowingteachers #createandeducate #diversebooks

node.text:
This stage in my classroom increases my students' confidence when they step on it! This year I wanted to place a quote on it so they always remember how important they are! My Cricut Joy machine made it so easy to transform this stage! #sponsored 

I love using my Cricut in the classroom! The Cricut Joy is so light weight and it's so easy to transport from school to home. This project was very simple to do and it really brightened up the classroom stage! I can't wait to continue using my @officialcricut throughout the school year! #cricutmade

node.text:
Hey you, yes you! You’re amazing and ASTROBRIGHTS® Papers wants to help teachers get EVERYTHING on their Back To School List. Astrobrights loves teachers so much that they’re giving away $2K and teacher tools not just to you, but to a teacher you nominate too! I personally love using their Happy Envelopes and their Joyful Mega Collection in my classroom because they really brighten everything up! #ad
 
I use @astrobrights papers for everything back to school! From bulletin boards, newsletters, to reading and math stations. I also love using them for crafts with the students! I love doing origami in the classroom, and students get so excited when choosing their favorite bright color! It’s super easy to get Astrobrights paper packs on @amazon so make sure to add it to your list for back to school this year!
#colorizeyourclassroom #astrobrightsteacher #bts2021

node.text:
Ready-to-Read books FLY off of my bookshelves! I kid you not, the bin is always empty and the books are always in students’ hands! (Which is everything my teacher heart wants!) My students love reading these books from @SimonKids and I love how they’re tailored towards students who are beginning their reading journey!
 
That’s why I’m so happy to now add Ready-to-Read Graphics to my shelves! #ad These leveled readers are inspired by the design of traditional graphic novels and even include a how-to guide on how to follow the panels and speech bubbles. Starting TODAY, you can check out three brand-new, entertaining #ReadytoReadGraphics series: Thunder Cluck, Nugget and Dog, and Geraldine Pu! Swipe to see sneak peeks!

node.text:
What this area used to look like ➡️ what it looks like right now! 👀 
.
What a difference! I loved this side of my classroom and I’m so sad to see it go! I am packing up the room because our school is under construction! Within the next year we will have new rooms which will be amazing though!

node.text: Unexpected last day of school today. (It was supposed to be this Friday) We got an e-mail at 1:20pm stating that our last day with the kids was going to be today due to the heat. With no air conditioning our classrooms felt like saunas! Definitely the weirdest/saddest way to end the year but nothing surprises us after this 2020-2021 school year.  #WeMadeIt #NowToPackUpTheRoom
